  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Surgical site infections (SSIs) are one of the major hospital acquired infections and&#xD;
      responsible for the most cost among the hospital acquired infections. The objective of this&#xD;
      study is to assess the neutrophil functional profiles and their associations with SSIs.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
